    "Figure 5 presents the comparison results in relation to scale variations.",
    "Segmentation performance is represented by three metrics (i.e., IoU, F β, and E φ).",
    "Some sample images with different scales of polyps are shown in Fig. 6.",
    "Visual comparison results of the scale variation evaluation are shown in Table 7.",
    "According to the results, we can draw the following conclusions: (1) In terms of overall performance, DuAT [62] and FeDNet [70] perform better across all types, and (2) vertical analysis reveals that most models achieve better performance in segmenting \"medium\" polyps while they exhibit relatively lower performance in segmenting other types."
